::DarkMouse::

She kept walking, slowly, but at least walking.  She looked down the 
hallway. "Which one is my room? She hoped it wouldn't be close to 
Quickstrike's room.  She felt like she had bothered him enough.  She 
didn't want to get him mad at her. "Um, thanks for helping me out. I 
really appreciate it." still holding onto him.

She took a couple more steps and wondered how much more the shaking 
would last. It was bothering her.
